context: <a0_0><a2_0><b3_0><b5_0>Sherman Ave<b5_0/><b3_0/><a2_0/><a0_0/> is a humor website that formed in January 2011. The website often publishes content about Northwestern student life, and most of Sherman Ave's staffed writers are current Northwestern undergraduate students writing under <a1_0><b4_0>pseudonyms<b4_0/><a1_0/>. The publication is well known among students for its interviews of prominent campus figures, its "Freshman Guide", its live-tweeting coverage of football games, and its satiric campaign in autumn 2012 to end the Vanderbilt University football team's clubbing of baby seals.
